WEBVTT

00:01.542 --> 00:02.500
<i>PREVIOUSLY ON</i>
<i>"RED BAND SOCIETY"...</i>

00:02.583 --> 00:03.959
YOU JUST GAVE ME NIPLASH!

00:04.041 --> 00:06.542
THIS WATER SUCKS!
IT TASTES LIKE PEE.

00:06.625 --> 00:08.750
WHY IS IT THAT
THE TWO MOST ELIGIBLE BACHELORS

00:08.834 --> 00:11.000
CAN ONLY SPORT WOOD
FOR A BAG OF BONES?

00:11.083 --> 00:12.625
Leo: I BROKE THINGS OFF,
AND I REGRETTED IT.

00:12.709 --> 00:14.250
I'M READY TO PUT THE PAST
BEHIND US IF YOU ARE.

00:14.333 --> 00:15.625
FRIENDS?
FRIENDS.

00:15.709 --> 00:16.875
HEY.

00:16.959 --> 00:18.750
LOOK,
I HAD AN AMAZING TIME,

00:18.834 --> 00:21.083
BUT IT'S A LITTLE STRANGE THAT
YOU TRACKED ME DOWN AT WORK.

00:21.166 --> 00:22.542
I AM VISITING MY SON.

00:22.625 --> 00:24.458
WHO'S YOUR SON?
Jordi: MOM?

00:24.542 --> 00:27.166
WE WERE UNDER THE IMPRESSION
THAT YOU HAD PASSED AWAY.

00:27.250 --> 00:28.834
SHE'S DEAD TO ME.

00:28.917 --> 00:30.083
MAYBE YOUR MOM BEING HERE
IS ACTUALLY A GOOD THING.

00:30.166 --> 00:31.250
RESEARCH SHOWS
THAT PATIENTS HAVE

00:31.333 --> 00:33.333
A MUCH BETTER CHANCE
OF SURVIVAL

00:33.417 --> 00:35.458
WHEN THEY HAVE SOMEONE
CLOSE TO THEM BY THEIR SIDE.

00:35.542 --> 00:36.709
I HEAR YOU'RE STICKING AROUND
FOR A WHILE.

00:36.792 --> 00:38.291
IT LOOKS THAT WAY.

00:38.375 --> 00:41.208
-- Captions by VITAC --
www.vitac.com

00:41.291 --> 00:43.500
[ MID-TEMPO GUITAR MUSIC PLAYS ]

00:47.041 --> 00:49.208
Charlie: <i>MY DAD ONCE TOLD ME</i>
<i>THAT GOING HOME</i>

00:49.291 --> 00:52.000
<i>IS NEVER AS EASY OR AS SIMPLE</i>
<i>AS WE PREDICT.</i>

00:53.000 --> 00:55.583
<i>LIKE STEPPING</i>
<i>INTO THE SAME RIVER TWICE,</i>

00:55.667 --> 00:57.500
<i>YOU NEVER KNOW WHAT AWAITS YOU</i>

00:57.583 --> 00:59.500
<i>WHEN YOU WALK THROUGH</i>
<i>THAT DOOR.</i>

00:59.583 --> 01:03.458
<i>BECAUSE GOING HOME MEANS FACING</i>
<i>EVERYTHING YOU LEFT BEHIND.</i>

01:08.667 --> 01:12.125
<i>MAYBE YOU LEFT GLORY AND FAME.</i>

01:17.417 --> 01:21.041
<i>OR MAYBE YOU LEFT FRIENDS.</i>

01:24.834 --> 01:28.667
<i>OR MAYBE YOU NEVER HAD ANY</i>
<i>TO BEGIN WITH.</i>

01:28.750 --> 01:32.041
<i>OR MAYBE YOU'VE SIMPLY ACQUIRED</i>
<i>TOO MUCH BAGGAGE ALONG THE WAY.</i>

01:32.125 --> 01:34.583
<i>BUT THE THING ABOUT HOME</i>
<i>IS THAT WE CAN'T STOP HOPING</i>

01:34.667 --> 01:39.583
<i>IT'LL ALWAYS BE</i>
<i>EXACTLY AS WE LEFT IT.</i>

01:39.959 --> 01:41.417
WHAT --
YOU ONLY BROUGHT TWO BAGS

01:41.500 --> 01:43.208
FOR THE MOST IMPORTANT NIGHT
OF MY LIFE?

01:43.291 --> 01:44.542
I'M SORRY.

01:44.625 --> 01:46.625
IT'S ALL I COULD CARRY
ON MY BIKE.

01:46.709 --> 01:48.500
WELL,
THEN GET A BIGGER BIKE.

01:48.583 --> 01:50.667
I'M GOING TO HOMECOMING,
NOT A YOGA CLASS.

01:50.750 --> 01:53.041
NOBODY EVEN CARES
WHAT YOU'RE WEARING TONIGHT.

01:53.125 --> 01:54.750
EVERYONE JUST MISSES YOU.

01:54.834 --> 01:57.542
ZUP! SELL THAT SUNSHINE
SOMEWHERE ELSE.

01:57.625 --> 01:58.959
WE BOTH KNOW THAT ABSENCE

01:59.041 --> 02:00.542
DOES NOT MAKE THE HEART
GROW FONDER.

02:00.625 --> 02:02.959
IT JUST MAKES PEOPLE
FORGET ABOUT YOU.

02:03.041 --> 02:06.875
LUCKILY, MY STAY IN THIS
HELLHOLE IS TEMPORARY.

02:06.959 --> 02:08.792
I JUST NEED
TO GET BACK TO SCHOOL

02:08.875 --> 02:11.834
AND REMIND PEOPLE
THAT I'M STILL IN CHARGE.

02:11.917 --> 02:13.667
I'M SURE IT'LL BE PERFECT,

02:13.750 --> 02:16.125
JUST LIKE LAST YEAR'S
HOMECOMING.

02:16.208 --> 02:18.542
[ TIESTO'S "LET'S GO" PLAYS ]

02:20.250 --> 02:21.792
OOPS.

02:21.875 --> 02:24.500
NOW ALL WE HAVE TO DO IS
FIGURE OUT YOUR EXIT STRATEGY.

02:24.583 --> 02:26.208
JUST KEEP UNPACKING.

02:26.291 --> 02:28.959
I HAVE MY OWN PLAN FOR DEALING
WITH NURSE RATCHED.

02:29.041 --> 02:30.750
[ MID-TEMPO ROCK MUSIC PLAYS ]

02:41.125 --> 02:44.041
[ I.V. STAND CLATTERS ]

02:47.500 --> 02:48.959
LOSE SOMETHING?

02:49.041 --> 02:50.083
YEP.

02:50.166 --> 02:51.583
ALL OF MY SOCCER SKILLS.

02:51.667 --> 02:53.000
MY KICK, MY DRIBBLING.

02:53.083 --> 02:55.500
LEO, YOU JUST STARTED
PHYSICAL THERAPY.

02:55.583 --> 02:58.125
REGAINING THAT KIND OF AGILITY
COULD TAKE MONTHS.

02:58.208 --> 02:59.250
I DON'T HAVE MONTHS.

02:59.333 --> 03:01.083
I GOT AN E-MAIL THIS MORNING

03:01.166 --> 03:02.625
FROM A STANFORD
ATHLETIC RECRUITER,

03:02.709 --> 03:04.166
AND HE SAYS HE SAW ME PLAY
LAST FALL,

03:04.250 --> 03:05.875
AND HE WANTS ME
ON THEIR TEAM NEXT YEAR.

03:05.959 --> 03:08.667
BUT HE DOESN'T KNOW
WHAT HAPPENED TO ME --

03:08.750 --> 03:10.583
YOU KNOW ABOUT, UH,
MY LEG.

03:10.667 --> 03:13.625
IF I DON'T HAVE SOCCER,
I DON'T GET A SCHOLARSHIP.

03:13.709 --> 03:16.750
IF I DON'T GET A SCHOLARSHIP,
I DON'T GO TO COLLEGE.

03:16.834 --> 03:20.375
WELL, YOU'RE WALKING,
AREN'T YOU?

03:20.458 --> 03:22.166
WELL, WHAT DOES THAT HAVE TO DO
WITH ANYTHING?

03:22.250 --> 03:24.709
IT WASN'T SO LONG AGO YOU WERE
WORRIED YOU'D NEVER WALK AGAIN.

03:24.792 --> 03:26.125
WALKING IS ONE THING.

03:26.208 --> 03:28.000
PLAYING DIVISION 1 SOCCER
IS NEXT LEVEL.

03:28.083 --> 03:30.291
THERE'S NO P.T. AT OCEAN PARK
THAT CAN TRAIN ME LIKE THAT.

03:30.375 --> 03:33.041
WHO SAID YOU HAD TO TRAIN
IN THE HOSPITAL?

03:33.125 --> 03:35.917
YOU DO SOME RESEARCH.
I'LL MAKE SOME CALLS.

03:37.333 --> 03:38.583
I SERIOUSLY WANT TO HUG YOU
RIGHT NOW.

03:38.667 --> 03:41.000
YOU'LL GET OVER IT.

03:44.959 --> 03:46.917
[ COMPUTER BEEPS ]

03:47.000 --> 03:48.792
YOU ONLINE SHOPPING?

03:48.875 --> 03:50.959
I BROKE UP WITH MY BOYFRIEND,

03:51.041 --> 03:54.959
SO I WAS SWITCHING MY
RELATIONSHIP STATUS TO "SINGLE."

03:55.041 --> 03:56.458
GEEZ, I'M SORRY.
ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

03:56.542 --> 03:58.542
ME? OH, YEAH.
YEAH.

03:58.625 --> 04:00.333
I'M -- I'M GREAT.
I'M GREAT.

04:00.417 --> 04:01.875
SO I LEFT MY FRIENDS
AND MY FAMILY

04:01.959 --> 04:03.375
AND MOVED OUT HERE
TO BE WITH HIM.

04:03.458 --> 04:04.917
SO WHAT?

04:05.000 --> 04:07.834
LIFE HAPPENS, RIGHT?

04:07.917 --> 04:09.750
WELL, THE BEST PART ABOUT
THIS JOB IS IT NEVER STOPS.

04:09.834 --> 04:11.500
YOU IMMERSE YOURSELF
IN YOUR WORK,

04:11.583 --> 04:14.125
AND BEFORE YOU KNOW IT, YOU
WON'T EVEN REMEMBER HIS NAME.

04:17.917 --> 04:19.417
IT'S BEN.

04:19.500 --> 04:21.959
HIS NAME WAS BEN.

04:37.917 --> 04:39.500
[ DOOR OPENS ]

04:39.583 --> 04:42.291
Eva: JORDI, I'M HERE.

04:42.375 --> 04:44.166
HI.

04:44.250 --> 04:46.417
I THOUGHT YOU WERE COMING
THIS MORNING.

04:46.500 --> 04:47.792
I KNOW, I'M SORRY.

04:47.875 --> 04:49.667
BUT I STOPPED
TO PICK THIS UP FOR YOU.

04:49.750 --> 04:54.208
I SAW IT ON "SEX AND THE CITY"
WHEN SAMANTHA HAD CANCER.

04:54.291 --> 04:55.834
THANK GOD FOR HBO.

04:57.875 --> 04:59.542
WHAT'S WITH YOUR OUTFIT?

04:59.625 --> 05:01.917
WELL,
I WAS AT A JOB INTERVIEW.

05:04.000 --> 05:07.166
YOU ALREADY HAVE A JOB --
AS A WAITRESS IN FRESNO.

05:07.250 --> 05:10.083
PRETTY TOUGH COMMUTE TO L.A.,
HUH?

05:10.166 --> 05:11.125
MOM, YOU DON'T HAVE TO --

05:11.208 --> 05:12.792
LOOK, WHEN YOU GET OUT,

05:12.875 --> 05:14.667
WE'LL HAVE AN APARTMENT,
I'LL HAVE A GREAT JOB,

05:14.750 --> 05:17.333
AND THIS WHOLE ORDEAL WILL JUST
BE A BLIP ON OUR RADAR.

05:17.417 --> 05:20.333
AND WHAT IF I NEVER
GET OUT?

05:20.417 --> 05:22.291
YOU WILL.
YOU DON'T KNOW THAT.

05:22.375 --> 05:24.041
YES, I DO.
HOW?

05:24.125 --> 05:26.375
BECAUSE I AM YOUR MOTHER
AND I SAID SO.

05:26.458 --> 05:30.458
SO LET ME DO THE WORRYING.

05:30.542 --> 05:33.750
YOU JUST FOCUS
ON GETTING BETTER, OKAY?

06:05.375 --> 06:07.250
Dash:
WHOA. CHEWING?

06:07.333 --> 06:10.083
WHEN'S THE LAST TIME
YOU FLEXED YOUR JAW MUSCLES?

06:10.166 --> 06:12.125
YEAH, WHY AREN'T YOU EATING WITH
YOUR REXO FRIENDS OVER THERE?

06:12.208 --> 06:14.417
THEY'RE NOT MY FRIENDS.

06:17.417 --> 06:19.208
WHAT DO YOU WANT?
Dash:
I'M JUST WONDERING...

06:19.291 --> 06:21.667
WHO GETS THE ROSE ON THE LATEST
EPISODE OF "CANCER BACHELOR"?

06:21.750 --> 06:24.333
IS IT
LATINO HEARTTHROB JORDI

06:24.417 --> 06:26.625
OR THE HOMETOWN FAVORITE,
LEO?

06:26.709 --> 06:29.041
WELL, NOT THAT IT'S
ANY OF YOUR BUSINESS,

06:29.125 --> 06:31.166
BUT...I'M NOT INTO
EITHER OF THEM.

06:31.250 --> 06:32.375
FINE.

06:32.458 --> 06:33.875
I'M JUST SAYING,
YOU KNOW,

06:33.959 --> 06:35.625
DON'T MESS WITH MY BOY LEO'S
HEAD LIKE THAT.

06:35.709 --> 06:38.667
YOU HAVE AN UNHEALTHY INTEREST
IN LEO'S DATING LIFE.

06:38.750 --> 06:41.083
I'M JUST INQUISITIVE.
INQUISITIVE...

06:41.166 --> 06:44.583
IN LOVE WITH HIM --
CALL IT WHATEVER YOU WANT.

06:44.667 --> 06:46.709
IF I WAS IN LOVE WITH HIM,

06:46.792 --> 06:50.000
I'D BE CLEAR ABOUT IT
BECAUSE MEN ARE DIRECT.

06:56.125 --> 06:57.792
WHAT'S UP, LADIES?

06:59.667 --> 07:01.291
[ <i>A GREAT BIG WORLD'S</i>
<i>"SAY SOMETHING" PLAYS</i> ]

07:01.375 --> 07:03.083
♪ <i>SAY SOMETHING,</i>
<i>I'M GIVING UP ON YOU</i> ♪

07:03.166 --> 07:06.667
I COULD POTENTIALLY NEVER LIVE
TO SEE ANOTHER HOMECOMING AGAIN,

07:06.750 --> 07:09.959
WHICH WOULD BE AMONG THE WORLD'S
GREATEST TRAGEDIES --

07:10.041 --> 07:11.792
SECOND ONLY
TO THE <i>TITANIC</i>

07:11.875 --> 07:15.667
OR NICKI MINAJ'S PERFUME,
"MINAJESTY."

07:15.750 --> 07:18.834
OR --
ME AND BEN BREAKING UP.

07:20.750 --> 07:22.542
♪ <i>ANYWHERE,</i>
<i>I WOULD HAVE FOLLOWED YOU</i> ♪

07:22.625 --> 07:26.500
NURSE JACKSON, IF I DON'T GO
TO THIS HOMECOMING, I JUST...

07:26.583 --> 07:28.291
[ SOBBING ]

07:28.375 --> 07:30.250
<i>AND THE OSCAR FOR THE MOST</i>
<i>PATHETIC PERFORMANCE</i>

07:30.333 --> 07:33.166
<i>IN A PEDIATRIC WARD</i>
<i>GOES TO...</i>

07:33.250 --> 07:36.208
KARA, SAVE THE TEARS
FOR YOUR HOMECOMING-QUEEN
ACCEPTANCE SPEECH.

07:36.291 --> 07:37.417
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

07:37.500 --> 07:38.792
WAIT.
DOES THAT MEAN I CAN GO?

07:38.875 --> 07:40.834
THIS IS A HOSPITAL,
NOT A PRISON.

07:40.917 --> 07:44.667
YES, YOU CAN GO...WITH A HEART
MONITOR AND A CHAPERONE.

07:44.750 --> 07:46.458
OKAY,
THIS I CAN WORK WITH,

07:46.542 --> 07:49.500
BUT THERE'S NO WAY I'M GOING
TO HOMECOMING WITH YOU.

07:49.583 --> 07:53.250
HOW WILL I EVER RECOVER
FROM SUCH A CRUSHING BLOW?

07:53.333 --> 07:55.250
PICK ME. PICK ME. PICK ME.
PICK ME. PICK ME. PICK ME.

07:55.333 --> 07:56.917
YOU CAN GO WITH BRITTANY.
[ GASPS ]

07:57.000 --> 07:58.875
[ BOTH GIGGLE ]

08:02.417 --> 08:03.709
Eva: MMM.

08:05.959 --> 08:09.166
WHAT DO YOU THINK THIS IS --
A VEGAS BUFFET?

08:09.250 --> 08:11.291
MMM.

08:11.375 --> 08:13.709
THESE ARE FOR JORDI.

08:13.792 --> 08:15.625
YOU WANT ONE?

08:15.709 --> 08:17.291
I BROUGHT YOU
SOME READING MATERIALS.

08:17.375 --> 08:19.291
NOW THAT WE'VE IDENTIFIED
JORDI'S CANCER

08:19.375 --> 08:21.083
AS EWING'S SARCOMA,

08:21.166 --> 08:23.125
YOU MIGHT WANT TO EDUCATE
YOURSELF ON HIS CONDITION.

08:23.208 --> 08:24.959
RIGHT.

08:25.041 --> 08:27.250
ALSO, THERE'S A PARENTS' SUPPORT
GROUP YOU SHOULD LOOK INTO.

08:27.333 --> 08:29.542
AND I'D LIKE TO GET
A BLOOD SAMPLE FROM YOU
AS SOON AS POSSIBLE.

08:29.625 --> 08:31.166
IT MIGHT BE USEFUL
DOWN THE LINE...

08:31.250 --> 08:33.792
BEFORE HIS NEXT SURGERY.

08:33.875 --> 08:35.667
THERE -- THERE'S GONNA BE
ANOTHER SURGERY?

08:35.750 --> 08:37.959
AT LEAST ONE.
POSSIBLY MORE.

08:38.041 --> 08:39.417
IT'S ALL IN THE PAMPHLETS.

08:39.500 --> 08:41.000
YOU DON'T LIKE ME,
DO YOU?

08:41.083 --> 08:43.291
I LIKE YOUR SON.

08:43.375 --> 08:45.291
WELL, I'M SORRY I MISSED
THE BEGINNING OF ALL THIS,

08:45.375 --> 08:47.041
BUT I'M HERE NOW,

08:47.125 --> 08:50.542
AND I REALLY APPRECIATE
YOUR HELP.

08:50.625 --> 08:52.375
WHAT DO YOU SAY?

08:52.458 --> 08:55.291
THE SUPPORT GROUP MEETS
AT 7:00 P.M. IN THE COMMISSARY.

08:57.625 --> 08:58.750
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

08:58.834 --> 09:01.750
IS EVERYTHING OKAY
IN THERE?

09:01.834 --> 09:03.792
♪ SUMMER COMES ♪

09:03.875 --> 09:05.125
WHAT DO YOU THINK?

09:05.208 --> 09:07.500
IT'S -- IT'S PINK.

09:07.583 --> 09:09.375
<i>THAT'S PUTTING IT KINDLY.</i>

09:09.458 --> 09:12.125
TOO MUCH PINK?

09:12.208 --> 09:14.792
IT'S KIND OF LIKE
STARING AT THE SUN.

09:14.875 --> 09:17.208
EVERY TIME I BLINK,
I SEE SPOTS.

09:17.291 --> 09:19.000
DR. McANDREW WAS RIGHT.

09:19.083 --> 09:22.458
IMMERSING YOURSELF IN YOUR WORK
IS THE BEST WAY TO GO.

09:22.542 --> 09:24.458
PLUS, I JUST LOVE HOMECOMINGS.
DON'T YOU?

09:24.542 --> 09:27.792
I WOULDN'T KNOW.
I HAVE NEVER BEEN.

09:27.875 --> 09:29.125
W--

09:29.208 --> 09:30.667
THIS MAY COME
AS A SHOCK TO YOU,

09:30.750 --> 09:33.875
BUT I WASN'T EXACTLY POPULAR
AT MY HIGH SCHOOL.

09:33.959 --> 09:35.667
WELL, THAT DOES COME
AS A SHOCK TO ME.

09:35.750 --> 09:37.417
I CAN'T IMAGINE ANYONE
NOT LIKING YOU.

09:37.500 --> 09:40.041
WELL, LUCKY ME --
I DON'T HAVE TO IMAGINE IT.

09:40.125 --> 09:41.917
I LIVED IT
ON A DAILY BASIS.

09:42.000 --> 09:43.458
♪ THERE'S NO NEED TO WORRY ♪

09:43.542 --> 09:45.250
AND THINGS ARE BETTER
HERE?

09:45.333 --> 09:47.792
DEFINITELY.
YEAH, MUCH BETTER.

09:47.875 --> 09:49.417
♪ JUST PLEASE DON'T SAY
YOU LOVE ME ♪

09:49.500 --> 09:50.917
♪ 'CAUSE I MIGHT NOT
SAY IT BACK ♪

09:51.000 --> 09:52.875
OOH!
WHAT IS HAPPENING
TO YOUR FACE?

09:52.959 --> 09:54.500
I AM HAVING
A LIGHT-BULB MOMENT.

09:54.583 --> 09:56.375
YOU SHOULD COME WITH ME
TO HOMECOMING.

09:56.458 --> 09:58.166
HARD PASS.

09:58.250 --> 10:00.583
I WOULD MUCH RATHER STAY HERE
AND STARE AT THE WALLS.

10:00.667 --> 10:02.709
THAT'S WHAT I'M
WORRIED ABOUT.

10:02.792 --> 10:06.166
I THINK YOU'RE GETTING
TOO COMFORTABLE IN THE HOSPITAL.

10:06.250 --> 10:10.166
AT SOME POINT, YOU'RE GONNA
HAVE TO GET BACK OUT THERE.

10:10.250 --> 10:13.917
THIS COULD BE A GOOD WAY TO EASE
BACK INTO THE SOCIAL SCENE.

10:14.000 --> 10:16.125
GOING TO A DANCE WHERE I WON'T
KNOW A SINGLE SOUL?

10:16.208 --> 10:17.333
YOU'LL KNOW KARA.

10:18.500 --> 10:19.959
YOU'LL KNOW ME.

10:22.500 --> 10:25.125
I THINK IT WOULD BE GOOD
FOR YOU.

10:25.208 --> 10:27.500
WAIT -- DO YOU HAVE
ANY MEDICAL STATISTICS

10:27.583 --> 10:28.792
TO BACK UP THIS THEORY?

10:28.875 --> 10:31.166
I'M NOT SAYING THIS
AS YOUR NURSE.

10:31.250 --> 10:33.333
I'M SAYING IT
AS YOUR FRIEND.

10:35.291 --> 10:37.291
I TAKE IT I DON'T HAVE
MUCH OF A CHOICE?

10:37.375 --> 10:39.291
NOPE.

10:39.375 --> 10:41.500
<i>HAVE YOU HEARD THE ONE</i>
<i>ABOUT THE NURSE, THE ANOREXIC,</i>

10:41.583 --> 10:43.625
<i>AND THE CHEERLEADER THAT ALL</i>
<i>WALK INTO A HOMECOMING?</i>

10:43.709 --> 10:44.709
<i>ME NEITHER.</i>

10:49.625 --> 10:52.208
SO, THE CLOSEST
PARALYMPIC CENTER

10:52.291 --> 10:54.792
WITH THE EQUIPMENT I NEED
TO TRAIN IS IN CHULA VISTA.

10:54.875 --> 10:57.166
IT SOUNDS LIKE A DOUGHNUT,
NOT A PLACE.

10:57.250 --> 10:59.625
IT'S ALSO THREE HOURS AWAY.
I KNOW.

10:59.709 --> 11:02.000
I CAN'T GET THERE ONCE A MONTH,
LET ALONE A FEW TIMES A WEEK.

11:02.083 --> 11:04.542
WELL, IT'S A GOOD THING
YOU DON'T HAVE TO.

11:05.458 --> 11:08.417
[ MID-TEMPO MUSIC PLAYS ]

11:08.500 --> 11:10.083
<i>EXCUSE ME AS I GEEK OUT,</i>

11:10.166 --> 11:12.500
<i>BUT I'M A GIANT FAN</i>
<i>OF THE BIONIC MAN.</i>

11:12.583 --> 11:15.125
<i>"TI" STANDS FOR TITANIUM</i>
<i>'CAUSE THAT'S WHAT</i>
<i>HIS LEG'S MADE OUT OF.</i>

11:15.208 --> 11:17.417
<i>STRONGEST ELEMENT IN THE WORLD.</i>

11:18.500 --> 11:20.500
NO OFFENSE, NURSE JACKSON,

11:20.583 --> 11:21.875
BUT I'M GONNA NEED MORE
THAN A YouTube VIDEO

11:21.959 --> 11:23.625
TO GET BACK INTO SHAPE.

11:23.709 --> 11:26.542
TI SPENT TWO MONTHS ON OUR FLOOR
WHEN HE WAS ABOUT YOUR AGE.

11:26.625 --> 11:29.041
THAT WAS BEFORE HE PLAYED
COLLEGE BALL AT UCLA

11:29.125 --> 11:30.750
AND THEN WENT PRO
IN EUROPE.

11:30.834 --> 11:32.542
I SPOKE TO HIM
THIS MORNING.

11:32.625 --> 11:34.959
YOU KNOW TIM "TI" JONES?

11:35.041 --> 11:36.500
STARTING NEXT WEEK,

11:36.583 --> 11:37.834
HE'S AGREED TO COME
TO THE HOSPITAL TO TRAIN YOU.

11:37.917 --> 11:39.291
SERIOUSLY?

11:39.375 --> 11:41.458
THAT'S INCREDIBLE.

11:41.542 --> 11:42.959
YOU'RE WELCOME.

11:43.041 --> 11:45.041
[ INDISTINCT P.A. CHATTER ]

11:54.417 --> 11:58.792
"NOVEL IMMUNOHISTOCHEMISTRY:
TECHNIQUES IN CANCER DIAGNOS--"

11:58.875 --> 12:01.041
WHAT IS THIS, SOME CASUAL
AFTERNOON READING?

12:01.125 --> 12:02.375
[ P.A. CHATTER CONTINUES ]

12:02.458 --> 12:04.166
NURSE JACKSON
GAVE THESE TO ME

12:04.250 --> 12:06.291
TO GET CAUGHT UP
ON JORDI'S CONDITION.

12:06.375 --> 12:08.291
THAT'S NOT
GETTING CAUGHT UP.

12:08.375 --> 12:10.083
THAT'S WHAT I READ IN MY THIRD
YEAR OF ONCOLOGY RESIDENCY.

12:10.166 --> 12:11.792
NO KIDDING.

12:11.875 --> 12:13.917
I DIDN'T KNOW I HAD TO GO TO
MEDICAL SCHOOL TO BE A MOTHER.

12:14.000 --> 12:15.375
YOU DON'T.

12:15.458 --> 12:16.959
IT KIND OF FEELS LIKE IT.

12:17.041 --> 12:18.792
I'M TURNING MY WHOLE LIFE
UPSIDE DOWN

12:18.875 --> 12:22.250
TO BE HERE FOR MY KID,
BUT IF NOBODY WANTS ME...

12:23.625 --> 12:26.875
JORDI WANTS YOU, AND YOU ARE
GONNA GET THROUGH THIS.

12:26.959 --> 12:28.458
RIGHT,
ONE DAY AT A TIME,

12:28.542 --> 12:30.208
LIKE EVERY OTHER PARENT IN HERE
WITH A SICK KID.

12:30.291 --> 12:31.667
I PROMISE YOU.

12:35.667 --> 12:39.667
NOW, LET ME BORROW THIS
FOR A BIT.

12:45.917 --> 12:48.250
HEY.

12:48.333 --> 12:51.500
WAS THIS
REALLY NECESSARY?

12:51.583 --> 12:52.917
[ SIGHS ]

12:53.000 --> 12:54.667
CAN'T A WOMAN
ENJOY THE SIMPLE PLEASURE

12:54.750 --> 12:57.041
OF GETTING HER BACK RUBBED
BY A CHAIR?

12:57.125 --> 12:58.166
I HAVE SO LITTLE.

12:58.250 --> 12:59.583
JUST DO ME A FAVOR.

12:59.667 --> 13:01.291
WILL YOU JUST LAY OFF
EVA PALACIOS?

13:01.375 --> 13:03.125
SHE'S GOT ENOUGH
TO WORRY ABOUT

13:03.208 --> 13:05.083
WITHOUT YOU
HUNTING HER FOR SPORT.

13:05.166 --> 13:06.917
UM, I WAS TRYING
TO EDUCATE HER,

13:07.000 --> 13:09.417
AND MAYBE IF YOU STOPPED
LISTENING TO LITTLE McANDREW,

13:09.500 --> 13:11.542
YOU'D REALIZE THAT WOMAN
ISN'T TO BE TRUSTED.

13:11.625 --> 13:14.834
I AM NOT LISTENING
WITH LITTLE McANDREW, ALL RIGHT?

13:14.917 --> 13:17.125
I'M LISTENING TO JORDI.

13:17.208 --> 13:19.291
JORDI WANTS
HIS MOTHER AROUND.

13:19.375 --> 13:21.375
JORDI <i>NEEDS</i>
HIS MOTHER AROUND.

13:21.458 --> 13:23.750
WELL, MY GUT TELLS ME
THAT WOMAN IS BAD NEWS,

13:23.834 --> 13:25.083
AND MY GUT IS NEVER WRONG.

13:25.166 --> 13:26.750
I'M NOT SAYING
SHE'S PERFECT.

13:26.834 --> 13:28.417
I'M JUST SAYING
SHE'S TRYING.

13:28.500 --> 13:30.291
WELL, MAYBE SHE SHOULD HAVE
TRIED HARDER

13:30.375 --> 13:31.625
WHILE SHE WAS RAISING HIM.

13:31.709 --> 13:34.542
EXCEPT SHE DIDN'T RAISE HIM,
DID SHE?

13:34.625 --> 13:36.333
NO, SHE DUMPED HIM OFF
AT GRANDMA'S

13:36.417 --> 13:38.125
SO SHE COULD DO
WHATEVER SHE WANTED.

13:38.208 --> 13:40.875
DO YOU KNOW HOW MANY PEOPLE
WOULD KILL FOR THE OPPORTUNITY

13:40.959 --> 13:42.166
TO RAISE THEIR OWN CHILD --

13:42.250 --> 13:43.709
THE THINGS THAT PEOPLE
WILL SACRIFICE

13:43.792 --> 13:46.417
JUST FOR THE PRIVILEGE
OF HAVING A BOY LIKE JORDI?

13:46.500 --> 13:49.208
AND THAT WOMAN JUST GAVE HIM UP
LIKE IT WAS NOTHING.

13:49.291 --> 13:51.875
PEOPLE MAKE MISTAKES.

13:51.959 --> 13:54.166
DOESN'T MEAN
I HAVE TO FORGIVE THEM.

13:54.250 --> 13:56.375
[ SIGHS ]

13:57.750 --> 14:01.208
IT MUST BE NICE TO ALWAYS BE
SO RIGHT ABOUT EVERYTHING, HUH?

14:01.291 --> 14:03.458
IT'S MY CROSS TO BEAR.

14:03.542 --> 14:05.583
[ CHAIR VIBRATING ]

14:08.458 --> 14:10.208
♪ I THINK IT'S TIME
THAT I MENTIONED ♪

14:10.291 --> 14:12.166
♪ I'VE GOT MYSELF AN OBSESSION ♪

14:12.250 --> 14:14.417
♪ FOR THE SMELL, FOR THE TOUCH ♪

14:14.500 --> 14:16.166
♪ KEEP THAT SCRUFF
LOOKIN' ROUGH ♪

14:16.250 --> 14:18.250
♪ I KNOW I'VE GOT MYSELF
A HABIT ♪

14:18.333 --> 14:20.041
♪ BUT I GOTTA HAVE IT NOW ♪

14:20.125 --> 14:21.917
♪ I DON'T CARE WHERE,
WORK IT OUT ♪

14:22.000 --> 14:23.333
♪ LET ME BREAK IT DOWN ♪

14:23.417 --> 14:25.000
♪ I TRY ON ♪

14:25.083 --> 14:26.834
♪ TRY ON ♪
♪ I TAKE IT OFF ♪

14:26.917 --> 14:29.458
♪ TAKE IT OFF ♪
♪ SO, WHAT YOU GOT? ♪

14:29.542 --> 14:31.583
PERFECT.

14:31.667 --> 14:33.333
♪ GIVE ME BOOTS AND BOYS ♪

14:33.417 --> 14:35.375
♪ THEY BRING ME SO MUCH JOY ♪

14:35.458 --> 14:37.166
♪ THEY BRING ME JOY ♪

14:37.250 --> 14:38.959
♪ I GOTTA SAY IT ♪

14:39.041 --> 14:41.709
♪ I WEAR THEM BOTH SO PRETTY
AS I WALK IN THE CITY ♪

14:41.792 --> 14:44.625
♪ WATCH OUT, BOOTS AND BOYS ♪

14:44.709 --> 14:46.709
♪ GIVE ME BOOTS AND BOYS ♪

14:46.792 --> 14:48.834
I WANT TO HAVE SEX
WITH ME.

14:48.917 --> 14:51.083
♪ GIVE ME BOOTS AND BOYS ♪

14:57.583 --> 14:59.542
♪ BOOTS AND BOYS ♪

14:59.625 --> 15:00.959
♪ BOOTS AND BOYS ♪

15:01.041 --> 15:02.875
♪ THEY BRING ME SO MUCH JOY ♪

15:02.959 --> 15:05.417
♪ CRAZY FOR YOU, CRAZY FOR YOU ♪

15:05.500 --> 15:07.750
♪ BOOTS AND BOYS ♪

15:07.834 --> 15:11.083
♪ OHH ♪

15:11.166 --> 15:13.125
WHAT IS THAT DOING HERE?

15:13.208 --> 15:15.792
SURPRISE. WE'RE ALL GOING
TO HOMECOMING TOGETHER.

15:15.875 --> 15:17.750
HA! NOT A CHANCE.

15:17.834 --> 15:20.125
I'M NOT GOING
WITH POCA-HOTMESS.

15:20.208 --> 15:21.875
I TOLD YOU
THIS WAS A BAD IDEA.

15:21.959 --> 15:23.792
DO NOT LET HER GET
UNDER YOUR SKIN.

15:23.875 --> 15:25.333
OH, WELL, HOW COULD I?

15:25.417 --> 15:27.041
I WOULD HAVE TO GET PAST
ALL THE PEACH FUZZ FIRST.

15:27.125 --> 15:29.291
OH, MY GOD,
IS IT ON YOUR STOMACH, TOO?

15:29.375 --> 15:31.208
ARE YOU ALL FURRY
LIKE A BEAR?

15:31.291 --> 15:33.917
OKAY, SAY ONE MORE MEAN THING,
AND WE'RE LEAVING WITHOUT YOU.

15:34.000 --> 15:35.834
HELLO?
IT'S MY SCHOOL.

15:35.917 --> 15:37.625
HELLO?
I DON'T CARE.

15:38.458 --> 15:39.500
W--
OH.

15:39.583 --> 15:40.583
BUT SHE DOESN'T EVEN --

15:40.667 --> 15:42.083
WHAT --
OKAY. FINE.

15:42.166 --> 15:44.000
CAN WE JUST GO ALREADY?
GOD!

15:44.083 --> 15:47.333
♪ SHAKE IT, FLIP IT,
MOVE IT TO IT ♪

15:47.417 --> 15:50.125
♪ SAY HEY, PUT THE MUSIC ON,
LET IT PLAY ♪

15:50.208 --> 15:52.458
♪ IF IT FEELS GOOD,
LET ME HEAR YOU SAY ♪

15:52.542 --> 15:54.083
♪ TURN IT UP, TURN IT UP,
TURN IT UP ♪

15:54.166 --> 15:56.208
MNH-MNH.
SLOW YOUR ROLL, SKELETOR.

15:56.291 --> 15:58.041
JUST BECAUSE I LET YOU
COME WITH ME

15:58.125 --> 15:59.709
DOES NOT MEAN
THAT WE'VE JOINED

15:59.792 --> 16:01.792
THE SISTERHOOD
OF THE TRAVELING PANTIES.

16:01.875 --> 16:04.083
STARTING NOW,
WE'RE COMPLETE STRANGERS.

16:04.166 --> 16:05.792
FOR THE RECORD,
I WANT TO BE HERE

16:05.875 --> 16:08.709
ABOUT AS MUCH YOU WANT ME
TO BE HERE -- PROBABLY LESS.

16:08.792 --> 16:11.375
THAT'S NOT
HUMANLY POSSIBLE.

16:11.458 --> 16:13.917
CAN YOU JUST WAIT UNTIL
BRITTANY'S FINISHED
PARKING THE CAR?

16:14.000 --> 16:16.750
I'M SORRY.
DO I KNOW YOU?

16:16.834 --> 16:18.834
[ CARY BROTHERS'
"IF YOU WERE HERE" PLAYS ]

16:25.583 --> 16:28.208
♪ AND IF YOU WERE HERE ♪

16:28.291 --> 16:30.959
♪ I COULD DECEIVE YOU ♪

16:31.041 --> 16:32.375
UH, FULL DISCLOSURE --

16:32.458 --> 16:34.792
I STOLE THIS
OUT OF A DEAD GUY'S ROOM.

16:34.875 --> 16:36.834
♪ AND IF YOU WERE HERE ♪

16:36.917 --> 16:38.166
SHALL WE?

16:38.250 --> 16:43.959
♪ YOU WOULD BELIEVE ♪

16:44.041 --> 16:47.875
♪ BUT WOULD YOU SUSPECT ♪

16:47.959 --> 16:53.208
♪ MY EMOTIONS WANDERING, YEAH ♪

16:55.458 --> 16:56.917
[ PAPERMAPS' "REUNION" PLAYS ]

16:57.000 --> 16:59.041
I STILL CAN'T BELIEVE
YOU'RE HERE.

16:59.125 --> 17:01.000
WHY ARE YOU HERE,
EXACTLY?

17:01.083 --> 17:03.291
I THOUGHT YOU COULD USE
A FRIEND.

17:03.375 --> 17:06.959
YEAH, THIS IS SO NOT MY SCENE
ON EVERY POSSIBLE LEVEL.

17:07.041 --> 17:08.750
EVEN IF IT WAS MY SCHOOL,
I --

17:08.834 --> 17:10.458
OH, BUT IT IS, REALLY.

17:10.542 --> 17:12.250
WHEN YOU THINK ABOUT IT, ISN'T
EVERY HIGH SCHOOL THE SAME?

17:12.333 --> 17:15.208
YOU KNOW? I MEAN,
WHERE WOULD YOU BE RIGHT NOW?

17:15.291 --> 17:16.917
PROBABLY THERE.

17:17.000 --> 17:18.333
♪ WAKE ME OUT OF THIS SLUMBER ♪

17:18.417 --> 17:20.125
HONESTLY,
I WOULD BE LOOKING AT MY PHONE

17:20.208 --> 17:22.458
AS IF I WERE SENDING
AN IMPORTANT TEXT,

17:22.542 --> 17:24.959
BUT, REALLY, I WOULD JUST BE
READING MY BOOK.

17:25.041 --> 17:27.917
YOU WOULD BE READING A BOOK
AT A DANCE?

17:28.000 --> 17:29.917
"THE GOLDFINCH"
IS A LITERARY MASTERPIECE.

17:30.000 --> 17:31.500
YEAH, BUT IT'S --
IT'S A DANCE.

17:31.583 --> 17:32.834
THE WOMAN WON A PULITZER.

17:32.917 --> 17:34.208
I SAY IT AGAIN --
IT'S A DANCE.

17:34.291 --> 17:35.375
MOVING ON.

17:35.458 --> 17:38.959
I CAN ASSUME YOU WOULD BE...

17:39.041 --> 17:40.291
SOMEWHERE OVER THERE?

17:41.667 --> 17:44.166
IN THAT VICINITY, BUT, UH,
ALWAYS LOOKING OVER MY SHOULDER.

17:44.250 --> 17:45.583
LOOKING FOR
THE NEXT BEST THING?

17:45.667 --> 17:48.333
NO,
LOOKING FOR SOMETHING REAL.

17:48.417 --> 17:50.875
♪ I DON'T EVEN NEED
TO HEAR THE WORDS ♪

17:50.959 --> 17:52.959
♪ I PROMISED YOU A KEEPSAKE ♪

17:53.041 --> 17:55.041
♪ AND WHY SHOULD I CARE
ANYWAY? ♪

17:55.125 --> 17:56.583
I'M THIRSTY.

17:56.667 --> 17:59.041
HOW ABOUT I GO GET US
SOME REFRESHING, NUTRITIOUS

17:59.125 --> 18:01.166
CALORIE-FREE
BOTTLES OF WATER?

18:01.250 --> 18:02.875
SOUNDS LIKE A PLAN.

18:02.959 --> 18:04.917
♪ IF I STAGED A REUNION ♪

18:05.041 --> 18:08.500
♪ WOULD YOU COME OUT ANYWAY? ♪

18:08.583 --> 18:10.291
DUDE, YOU SUCK AT THIS.

18:10.375 --> 18:13.083
YOU HAVE NO POKER FACE
WHATSOEVER.

18:13.166 --> 18:15.458
MAYBE I DO.
MAYBE I DON'T.

18:15.542 --> 18:17.250
[ CHUCKLES ]
OKAY.

18:17.333 --> 18:19.000
I CALL.

18:23.291 --> 18:26.875
WHATEVER, MAN.
THIS GAME IS STUPID.

18:26.959 --> 18:28.375
HEY.

18:28.458 --> 18:29.709
HERE YOU ARE.

18:29.792 --> 18:31.083
I'VE BEEN LOOKING EVERYWHERE
FOR YOU.

18:31.166 --> 18:33.125
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU
STILL DOING HERE?

18:33.208 --> 18:35.625
I HAVE A PARENTS' MEETING
TONIGHT.

18:35.709 --> 18:37.709
HOW ARE YOU FEELING,
JO-JO?

18:37.792 --> 18:40.667
NOT GREAT, BUT ON THE UPSIDE,
I HAVEN'T PUKED YET.

18:40.750 --> 18:45.417
THEN WHY DON'T YOU HAVE FUN
WHILE YOU'RE STILL UP FOR IT?

18:45.500 --> 18:48.583
GO TO THE MOVIES
WITH YOUR FRIEND.

18:48.667 --> 18:50.417
HAVE SOME POPCORN.
BUY SOME ICEES.

18:50.500 --> 18:52.625
DO WHATEVER YOU WANT.
SERIOUSLY?

18:52.709 --> 18:54.667
BETTER TAKE THIS
BEFORE I CHANGE MY MIND.

18:55.917 --> 18:59.208
DUDE, YOUR MOM'S
KIND OF AWESOME, MAN.

18:59.291 --> 19:00.542
YOU HEAR THAT?

19:00.625 --> 19:03.041
EASY.
I'M KIND OF AWESOME.

19:03.125 --> 19:04.417
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GO.

19:06.959 --> 19:08.083
YOU GONNA BE HERE
WHEN I GET BACK?

19:08.166 --> 19:11.709
I GOT NOWHERE ELSE TO BE.

19:14.208 --> 19:17.917
OH, MY GOD.

19:18.000 --> 19:19.875
IN THIS LIGHT,
YOU LOOK EXACTLY LIKE

19:19.959 --> 19:21.750
BEYONCé'S CAUCASIAN
LITTLE SISTER.

19:21.834 --> 19:23.500
CAN I BORROW LIP GLOSS?
OF COURSE.

19:23.583 --> 19:24.875
BUT THERE ARE MUCH MORE PRESSING
MATTERS WE NEED TO DISCUSS.

19:24.959 --> 19:26.959
WAIT.
WHAT THE HELL?

19:27.041 --> 19:29.417
DID YOU NOT TELL QUINBY
I WAS WEARING SEQUINS?

19:29.500 --> 19:32.375
I TEXTED EVERYONE.

19:32.458 --> 19:34.542
MY GOD, THIS IS EXACTLY
WHAT I WAS TALKING ABOUT.

19:34.625 --> 19:36.834
THINGS ARE ALREADY SPIRALING
WAY OUT OF CONTROL.

19:36.917 --> 19:38.083
OKAY, BUT WE REALLY NEED
TO TALK.

19:38.166 --> 19:39.625
I CAN'T TALK RIGHT NOW.

19:39.709 --> 19:42.000
I NEED TO GO IN THERE
AND ASSERT MY POWER.

19:42.083 --> 19:44.583
<i>THIS IS WHAT YOU CALL</i>
<i>A KNIFE FIGHT IN BEVERLY HILLS.</i>

19:46.542 --> 19:48.041
[ GASPS ]
OOPS.

19:48.125 --> 19:49.500
<i>FIRST BLOOD TO THE BLONDE.</i>

19:49.583 --> 19:51.333
I TOTALLY RUINED
YOUR DRESS.

19:51.417 --> 19:53.333
I HOPE YOU BROUGHT
AN EXTRA ONE.

19:53.417 --> 19:55.542
KARA SOUDERS.

19:55.625 --> 19:57.417
♪ CAN'T FLY AWAY ♪

19:57.500 --> 19:59.750
[ SQUEALS ]
YOU LOOK AMAZE!

19:59.834 --> 20:01.041
GUYS,
DOESN'T SHE LOOK AMAZE?

20:01.125 --> 20:03.375
<i>OKAY, THIS IS WEIRD.</i>

20:03.458 --> 20:05.291
WELCOME BACK,
GIRLFRIEND.

20:05.375 --> 20:07.458
IT'S GOOD TO BE BACK,
BITCHES.

20:07.542 --> 20:09.625
<i>AND ALL IS RIGHT</i>
<i>IN KARA'S WORLD.</i>

20:09.709 --> 20:11.291
<i>OR IS IT?</i>

20:11.375 --> 20:14.542
LEO ROTH?

20:14.625 --> 20:16.166
DAVE, WHAT UP?

20:16.250 --> 20:17.333
YOU'RE ALIVE.

20:17.417 --> 20:18.583
LAST TIME I CHECKED.

20:18.667 --> 20:20.458
HEY, IT'S GOOD TO SEE YOU,
DUDE.

20:20.542 --> 20:21.667
YEAH.

20:21.750 --> 20:23.375
YOU LOOK...

20:23.458 --> 20:25.500
BALD.

20:25.583 --> 20:26.917
YEAH, BUT COOL BALD.

20:27.000 --> 20:28.667
I'M SORRY
IF THAT CAME OUT WEIRD.

20:28.750 --> 20:31.625
IT'S JUST I HAVEN'T SEEN YOU
SINCE, UH...

20:31.709 --> 20:33.417
CANCER?

20:33.500 --> 20:36.000
I WAS GOING TO SAY MODESTO --
NATIONALS.

20:36.083 --> 20:38.458
OH, RIGHT, WHEN I MEGGED YOU
FOR THE WIN IN OVERTIME. YEAH.

20:38.542 --> 20:40.792
SO, WHAT ARE YOU DOING
HERE? YOU GONNA COME TO
THIS SCHOOL NEXT SEMESTER?

20:40.875 --> 20:43.667
NO, I'M, UH, JUST CRASHING WITH
SOME FRIENDS FROM THE HOSPITAL.

20:43.750 --> 20:45.542
I DIDN'T REALIZE
YOU WERE STILL SICK.

20:45.625 --> 20:47.792
I'M NOT.
I'M STRONGER THAN EVER.

20:47.875 --> 20:52.000
I'M JUST GETTING A FEW KINKS
WORKED OUT OF MY NEW LEG.

20:52.083 --> 20:55.875
AND I SHOULD BE, UH,
BACK ON THE FIELDS BY PLAY-OFFS.

20:55.959 --> 20:57.542
COOL.

20:57.625 --> 20:59.542
YEAH, YOUR TEAM COULD REALLY USE
SOME OF YOUR, UH --

20:59.625 --> 21:01.709
YOUR, UH --
YOUR FIGHTING SPIRIT.

21:01.792 --> 21:03.083
MY SPIRIT?
[ CHUCKLES ]

21:03.166 --> 21:04.834
DUDE, WHAT ABOUT
MY CORNER KICKS?

21:04.917 --> 21:06.166
YEAH, SURE. THOSE, TOO.

21:06.250 --> 21:07.792
[ SIGHS ]

21:07.875 --> 21:09.375
HEY, I'M GLAD YOUR TEAM
MADE A PLACE FOR YOU.

21:09.458 --> 21:10.917
THEY DIDN'T MAKE A PLACE.

21:11.000 --> 21:13.166
MY TEAM SAVED MY SPACE
SO THAT THEY COULD WATCH ME

21:13.250 --> 21:15.041
HUMILIATE YOU
IN FRONT OF YOUR TEAM,

21:15.125 --> 21:16.166
LIKE I DID LAST SEASON.

21:16.250 --> 21:18.625
IT WAS GREAT SEEING YOU.

21:18.709 --> 21:20.792
[ HIP-HOP MUSIC PLAYING ]

21:30.667 --> 21:32.000
Brooklyn: CAN WE TALK TO YOU
FOR A MINUTE?

21:33.500 --> 21:35.583
AM I SITTING
IN YOUR SEATS?

21:35.667 --> 21:37.625
I'M SO SORRY.
I CAN MOVE.

21:37.709 --> 21:40.166
OH, MY GOD. SHE LOOKS
EVEN BETTER WHEN SHE STANDS.

21:40.250 --> 21:41.500
WHAT?

21:41.583 --> 21:43.000
WELL, IT'S JUST THAT
WE'VE NEVER SEEN

21:43.083 --> 21:45.417
A SIZE TRIPLE-ZERO BEFORE
IN THE FLESH.

21:45.500 --> 21:47.250
♪ HARD TO GET AROUND
WITHOUT YOUR LOVE ♪

21:47.333 --> 21:49.083
YOU'RE A REAL UNICORN.

21:49.166 --> 21:51.291
RARE AND BEAUTIFUL.
MM-HMM.

21:51.375 --> 21:53.417
THANK YOU.
SO, WHAT'S YOUR SECRET?

21:53.500 --> 21:55.667
TWO CARDIO CLASSES ON WEDNESDAY?
TABATA BOOTCAMP?

21:55.750 --> 21:57.834
VISUAL EATING ON MONDAY,
GREEN JUICE ON FRIDAYS,

21:57.917 --> 21:58.875
AND NO FOOD ON SUNDAYS?

21:58.959 --> 22:00.291
NO, ACTUALLY, I, UM --

22:00.375 --> 22:02.834
I WAS DIAGNOSED
WITH AN EATING DISORDER.

22:02.917 --> 22:04.834
I LIVE
AT OCEAN PARK HOSPITAL.

22:04.917 --> 22:06.291
YOU'RE SO COMMITTED.

22:06.375 --> 22:08.542
I JUST DON'T HAVE
THE DISCIPLINE FOR THAT.

22:08.625 --> 22:09.959
WE NEED TO GET A PICTURE.

22:10.041 --> 22:12.125
[ GASPS ]
YOU ARE GONNA BE INSTA-FAMOUS.

22:12.208 --> 22:14.000
OKAY.

22:14.083 --> 22:16.834
♪ BOOM, BOOM, BOOMERANG ♪

22:16.917 --> 22:19.542
♪ BOOM, BOOM, BOOMERANG ♪

22:19.625 --> 22:20.834
♪ MM-HMM ♪

22:20.917 --> 22:22.625
<i>WITH FRIENDS LIKE THESE,</i>

22:22.709 --> 22:24.417
<i>EMMA MIGHT BE BETTER OFF</i>
<i>SITTING ALONE.</i>

22:24.500 --> 22:26.917
HEY, MAN,
YOU ALL RIGHT?

22:27.000 --> 22:30.417
AH, CHEMO IS GNARLY.
I FEEL LIKE ASS.

22:30.500 --> 22:32.000
[ SCOFFS ]

22:32.083 --> 22:33.750
HEY, MAN, AT LEAST THEY GOT YOU
ON A REGIMEN

22:33.834 --> 22:35.500
THAT LETS YOU KEEP
ALL YOUR HAIR,

22:35.583 --> 22:37.417
UNLIKE OUR BALD FRIEND,
LEO.

22:37.500 --> 22:39.667
HOMEBOY LOOKS LIKE
PROFESSOR XAVIER
OR SOMETHING, MAN.

22:39.750 --> 22:41.625
[ CHUCKLES ]
HE'S EVEN GOT THE WHEELCHAIR.

22:41.709 --> 22:43.041
OH, SNAP.

22:43.125 --> 22:45.625
SPEAKING OF LEO --
ACTUALLY, EMMA AND LEO --

22:45.709 --> 22:48.125
HOW YOU FEEL ABOUT
THAT WHOLE SITCH, MAN?

22:48.208 --> 22:50.625
AH, THAT'S WHY YOU'VE BEEN
HANGING OUT WITH ME TODAY.

22:50.709 --> 22:52.417
YOU'RE NOT INTERESTED
IN BEING MY FRIEND.

22:52.500 --> 22:54.500
YOU'RE INTERESTED IN PROTECTING
YOUR FRIENDSHIP WITH LEO,

22:54.583 --> 22:56.166
AND YOU'RE TRYING TO GET DIRT
ON ME FOR HIM.

22:56.250 --> 22:57.792
NO, MAN.
LOOK, I GOT NO PROBLEM WITH YOU.

22:57.875 --> 23:00.250
I'M JUST TRYING TO GET A LAY
OF THE LAND, THAT'S ALL.

23:00.333 --> 23:02.500
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
THE LAY OF THE LAND IS...

23:02.583 --> 23:03.917
MY LIFE IS WEIRDLY STABLE

23:04.000 --> 23:06.000
FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN BASICALLY FOREVER.

23:06.083 --> 23:07.417
MY MOM'S AROUND,

23:07.500 --> 23:09.792
AND I HAVE FRIENDS
THAT I ACTUALLY LIKE,

23:09.875 --> 23:11.250
INCLUDING YOU.

23:11.333 --> 23:14.000
I'M NOT ABOUT TO RUIN THAT
OVER A GIRL.

23:14.083 --> 23:15.041
COOL.

23:15.125 --> 23:16.500
BRO CODE.

23:16.583 --> 23:18.417
RED BAND CODE.

23:18.500 --> 23:20.166
AH.

23:20.250 --> 23:22.834
IT MUST BE WEIRD,
HAVING YOUR MOM COME AROUND

23:22.917 --> 23:24.250
AND BE ALL "MOM" ON YOU

23:24.333 --> 23:25.625
AFTER, YOU KNOW,
YOU'VE BEEN ON YOUR OWN.

23:25.709 --> 23:27.959
YEAH, IT'S KIND OF
WHAT SHE DOES.

23:28.041 --> 23:31.375
BEING A MOM FOR HER IS LIKE
GOING ON A CAMPING TRIP.

23:31.458 --> 23:33.083
[ SCOFFS ]
NO, I'M SERIOUS.

23:33.166 --> 23:35.000
SHE GETS ALL EXCITED
AND BUYS ALL THE EQUIPMENT,

23:35.083 --> 23:36.542
AND THEN TWO DAYS INTO IT,

23:36.625 --> 23:38.000
SHE WISHES THAT SHE WAS
BACK IN THE HOTEL.

23:38.083 --> 23:40.458
SHE CAME AROUND
WHEN YOU NEEDED HER MOST.

23:40.542 --> 23:43.875
SEEMS TO ME LIKE SHE REALLY
WANTS TO GO CAMPING, BRO.

23:46.041 --> 23:48.166
THEY BETTER HAVE
SOME GOOD POPCORN HERE,

23:48.250 --> 23:49.458
OR ELSE I'M GOING HOME.

23:49.542 --> 23:51.542
♪ UNH, TELL 'EM WHERE I'M FROM ♪

23:51.625 --> 23:53.250
♪ FINGER ON THE PUMP ♪

23:53.333 --> 23:55.083
♪ MAKE THE SIXTH STRAIGHT JUMP
FROM SoCAL ♪

23:55.166 --> 23:56.834
♪ HOLLYWOOD TO THE SLUMS ♪

23:56.917 --> 23:58.583
♪ CHRONIC SMOKE, GET BURNT
BY THE CALIFORNIA SUN ♪

23:58.667 --> 24:01.000
♪ ON THE WEST SIDE,
EAST COAST, WHERE YOU AT? ♪

24:01.083 --> 24:03.291
♪ JUST GOT TO NEW YORK
LIKE A GNAT ON A JET ♪

24:03.375 --> 24:05.458
♪ TO LONDON, TO BRAZIL,
TO QUéBEC ♪

24:05.542 --> 24:08.583
OH, MY GOSH.
YOU'RE HERE.

24:08.667 --> 24:11.458
I JUST WANT TO THANK YOU
FOR BEING SUCH AN INSPIRATION.

24:11.542 --> 24:13.875
I'M GLAD WE COULD
PUT THE PAST BEHIND US NOW.

24:13.959 --> 24:15.625
I'M SORRY.

24:15.709 --> 24:17.125
I DON'T KNOW WHY YOU THINK
IT'S OKAY TO BE TALKING TO ME.

24:17.208 --> 24:18.667
I LOVE YOU SO MUCH.

24:18.750 --> 24:20.750
OH, MY GOD!

24:20.834 --> 24:21.750
♪ I'M-A BE THERE IN A MINUTE,
I JUST BOOKED A PARIS TICKET ♪

24:21.834 --> 24:23.583
OH, MY GOD.

24:23.667 --> 24:26.000
SOMEONE NEEDS TO GO BREAK
THE REST OF BENT GIRL'S SPINE

24:26.083 --> 24:27.834
BECAUSE SHE LITERALLY
JUST RAPED ME.

24:27.917 --> 24:29.834
YOU MEAN ANNA?

24:29.917 --> 24:33.125
POOR THING.
SHE'S BEEN THROUGH SO MUCH...

24:33.208 --> 24:34.834
JUST LIKE YOU.

24:34.917 --> 24:36.583
JUST LIKE WHO?

24:36.667 --> 24:38.583
<i>HERE'S WHERE IT ALL GOES DARK.</i>

24:38.667 --> 24:41.458
ALSO, SHE'S BEEN SUPER HELPFUL
WITH YOUR PRESENTATION.

24:41.542 --> 24:44.667
WHAT?
WHAT PRESENTATION?

24:44.750 --> 24:47.583
OKAY, IT WAS SUPPOSED TO BE
A SURPRISE,

24:47.667 --> 24:49.000
BUT I CAN GIVE YOU
A SNEAK PEEK.

24:49.083 --> 24:51.041
♪ THIS IS HOW IT GOES ♪

24:51.125 --> 24:53.000
♪ UNH, TELL 'EM WHERE I'M AT ♪

24:53.083 --> 24:55.041
<i>KARA IS THE KINDEST,</i>
<i>MOST GENEROUS,</i>

24:55.125 --> 24:56.291
<i>PATIENT HUMAN I'VE EVER MET.</i>

24:56.375 --> 24:58.125
[ SCOFFS ]

24:58.208 --> 24:59.667
<i>IT'S SUCH A TRAGEDY</i>
<i>THAT THIS HAD TO HAPPEN TO HER,</i>

24:59.750 --> 25:01.333
<i>AND SHE WAS [SIGHS]</i>
<i>SO BEAUTIFUL,</i>

25:01.417 --> 25:04.000
<i>AND HER HEART IS SO...BROKEN.</i>

25:04.083 --> 25:05.750
WHAT? WHY?

25:05.834 --> 25:11.875
<i>KARA WAS LOVED BY VALETS</i>
<i>AND OLD PEOPLE</i>

25:11.959 --> 25:15.625
<i>AND HOMELESS PEOPLE...</i>
<i>AND ALL PEOPLE.</i>

25:15.709 --> 25:17.083
WHY ARE YOU DOING THIS?

25:17.166 --> 25:18.667
BECAUSE YOU'RE REALLY SICK,
AND YOU MIGHT DIE.

25:18.750 --> 25:21.750
WE FEEL
SUPER-DUPER BAD FOR YOU.

25:21.834 --> 25:23.750
WHAT?

25:23.834 --> 25:25.542
Charlie: <i>AND JUST LIKE THAT,</i>
<i>IT WENT FROM A HOMECOMING PARTY</i>

25:25.625 --> 25:26.750
<i>TO A PITY PARTY.</i>

25:26.834 --> 25:29.417
THANK YOU.
GOOD LUCK TO YOU.

25:29.500 --> 25:30.750
TAKE CARE.
BYE.

25:30.834 --> 25:32.542
HI.
HEY.

25:32.625 --> 25:34.417
HEY, DID, UH --

25:34.500 --> 25:37.291
DID YOU GIVE JORDI PERMISSION
TO GO TO THE MOVIES?

25:37.375 --> 25:40.291
NOT ONLY DID I GIVE HIM
PERMISSION -- I GAVE HIM $50.

25:40.375 --> 25:41.917
WHO TOLD YOU
YOU CAN DO THAT?

25:42.000 --> 25:44.250
YOU C--
YOU CAN'T JUST LET

25:44.333 --> 25:46.208
A SICK KID
WALK OUT OF A HOSPITAL.

25:46.291 --> 25:48.792
[ SIGHS ]
HE SEEMED FINE.

25:48.875 --> 25:51.333
HE'S NOT FINE.
HE HAS CANCER.

25:51.417 --> 25:52.917
HE HAS A MILLION
DIFFERENT CHEMICALS

25:53.000 --> 25:54.083
COURSING THROUGH
HIS BODY.

25:54.166 --> 25:55.750
HE NEEDS REST.

25:55.834 --> 25:57.583
UH, NEXT TIME YOU WANT TO DO
SOMETHING NICE FOR HIM,

25:57.667 --> 25:58.917
JUST CONSULT WITH ME FIRST.

25:59.000 --> 26:00.750
I'M SORRY.

26:00.834 --> 26:02.834
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T KNOW.

26:02.917 --> 26:05.000
ALL RIGHT. IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

26:05.083 --> 26:07.625
I KNOW IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY,
ALL RIGHT?

26:07.709 --> 26:10.125
IT SURE HAS.

26:10.208 --> 26:12.750
IN FACT,
I COULD USE A DRINK.

26:12.834 --> 26:14.709
YOU INTERESTED?

26:14.792 --> 26:15.834
[ SIGHS ]

26:15.917 --> 26:17.834
NO, I-I HAVE ROUNDS.

26:17.917 --> 26:19.875
IT'S OKAY.
WHAT TIME DO YOU GET OFF?

26:19.959 --> 26:22.834
EVA, I THOUGHT WE BOTH AGREED
THAT THIS CAN'T HAPPEN AGAIN.

26:24.208 --> 26:26.667
BUT YOU KEEP SENDING ME
MIXED SIGNALS.

26:26.750 --> 26:29.041
I-I-I'M SORRY.
I DON'T --

26:29.125 --> 26:30.500
[ CELLPHONE RINGS ]

26:30.583 --> 26:32.583
LET'S KEEP THE FOCUS
ON JORDI, OKAY?
YEAH.

26:32.667 --> 26:34.250
I UNDERSTAND WHAT YOU WERE
TRYING TO DO TODAY...

26:34.333 --> 26:36.375
MM-HMM.
...TRYING TO MAKE HIM HAPPY.

26:36.458 --> 26:39.166
THINGS ARE GONNA GET HARDER
BEFORE THEY GET EASIER.

26:39.250 --> 26:41.959
ALL RIGHT, THERE'S NOT ALWAYS
GONNA BE A QUICK FIX.

26:42.041 --> 26:43.583
ALL RIGHT?

26:43.667 --> 26:45.375
WHY DON'T YOU BE HIS DOCTOR
AND LET ME BE HIS MOTHER?

26:45.458 --> 26:47.333
ESTúPIDO.

26:47.417 --> 26:49.542
[ STRANGE TALK'S "MORNING SUN"
PLAYS ]

26:50.875 --> 26:52.542
♪ WE'LL WATCH THE MORNING SUN ♪

27:05.333 --> 27:08.041
SO MANY CUTE COUPLES.
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:08.125 --> 27:09.750
♪ MORNING SUN ♪

27:09.834 --> 27:11.917
♪ WE'LL WATCH THE MORNING SUN ♪

27:12.000 --> 27:13.583
♪ IF WE MAKE IT
THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

27:13.667 --> 27:15.834
[ Voice breaking ]
OH, THANK YOU.

27:15.917 --> 27:17.291
[ SNIFFLES ]

27:17.375 --> 27:18.542
ARE YOU HAVING FUN?

27:18.625 --> 27:19.959
YEAH.

27:20.041 --> 27:21.250
♪ IF WE MAKE IT
THROUGH THE NIGHT ♪

27:21.333 --> 27:24.375
♪ WE'LL WATCH THE MORNING SUN ♪

27:25.417 --> 27:26.875
HEY.
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

27:26.959 --> 27:28.125
I'M GETTING OUT OF HERE.

27:28.208 --> 27:29.583
EVERYONE IN THIS HELLCOMING

27:29.667 --> 27:31.583
IS OBSESSED WITH ME
AND MY HEART PROBLEM.

27:31.667 --> 27:33.125
WHAT'S WRONG WITH THAT?

27:33.208 --> 27:34.417
I THOUGHT YOU LIKED BEING
THE CENTER OF ATTENTION.

27:34.500 --> 27:36.291
YEAH, NOT THIS KIND
OF ATTENTION.

27:36.375 --> 27:39.750
I USED TO WALK DOWN THESE HALLS
LIKE I WAS FREAKING MOSES.

27:39.834 --> 27:41.875
THE CROWD WOULD PART
AT MY FEET,

27:41.959 --> 27:44.166
BUT NOW EVERYONE
IS COMING UP TO ME

27:44.250 --> 27:46.208
AND TALKING TO ME,
HUGGING ME.

27:46.291 --> 27:48.208
YOU KNOW THAT'S 'CAUSE
THEY CARE ABOUT YOU.

27:48.291 --> 27:49.583
[ SCOFFS ]
SCREW THAT NOISE.

27:49.667 --> 27:51.083
I'D RATHER BE FEARED
THAN LOVED.

27:51.166 --> 27:53.125
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHO ARE YOU? TONY SOPRANO?

27:53.208 --> 27:55.542
I MEAN, COME ON.
WHAT KIND OF PHILOSOPHY IS THAT?

27:55.625 --> 27:59.125
LOOK, YOU MIGHT GET OFF
ON BEING MR. CANCER BOY,

27:59.208 --> 28:01.542
BALD POSTER CHILD
LEGLESS MAN,

28:01.625 --> 28:05.458
BUT THE ONE THING I'M NOT OKAY
WITH IS BEING PITIED.

28:08.291 --> 28:09.500
[ MICROPHONE FEEDBACK ]

28:09.583 --> 28:11.792
Quinby:
GREETINGS, FELLOW VIKINGS.

28:11.875 --> 28:16.333
IT IS WITH GREAT HONOR
AND HUMBLENESS...ITY

28:16.417 --> 28:20.875
THAT I ANNOUNCE PARADISE COVE
HIGH'S 2014 HOMECOMING QUEEN,

28:20.959 --> 28:22.792
KARA SOUDERS.

28:22.875 --> 28:24.709
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

28:24.792 --> 28:26.208
HOP IN.

28:26.291 --> 28:27.500
I CAN WALK.

28:27.583 --> 28:29.000
ACTUALLY,
FOR INSURANCE PURPOSES,

28:29.083 --> 28:31.959
WE'RE GONNA NEED YOU TO GO AHEAD
AND TAKE A SEAT.

28:33.750 --> 28:35.750
[ CHEERS AND APPLAUSE ]

28:35.834 --> 28:38.667
<i>NOT QUITE THE CHARIOT</i>
<i>SHE WAS EXPECTING.</i>
COMING THROUGH!

28:42.041 --> 28:43.917
Woman over P.A.:
PAGING DR. STATEMAN.

28:44.000 --> 28:45.792
DR. STATEMAN, PLEASE.

28:54.583 --> 28:55.709
HOW'S IT GOING?

28:57.667 --> 29:00.375
FINE.

29:00.458 --> 29:01.834
[ SIGHS ]

29:01.917 --> 29:03.458
I KNOW I'VE FLOODED YOU
WITH MATERIAL,

29:03.542 --> 29:05.000
SO IF YOU HAVE QUESTIONS,

29:05.083 --> 29:07.417
I'M HAPPY TO WALK YOU THROUGH
ANYTHING.

29:07.500 --> 29:10.375
DO YOU THINK
I'M SOME KIND OF MORON?

29:10.458 --> 29:11.667
I'M JUST TRYING TO HELP.

29:11.750 --> 29:13.083
HMM.

29:13.166 --> 29:14.792
[ PEN CLICKS ]

29:14.875 --> 29:18.417
I'M SORRY IF I
CAME ACROSS HARSH EARLIER.

29:18.500 --> 29:19.458
HARSH?

29:19.542 --> 29:20.917
LADY, I CAN HANDLE HARSH.

29:21.000 --> 29:23.000
WHAT I CAN'T HANDLE
IS CONDESCENDING AND RUDE.

29:23.083 --> 29:25.375
TELL ME -- DO YOU HAVE ANY KIDS
OF YOUR OWN?

29:25.458 --> 29:27.542
I DON'T.

29:27.625 --> 29:30.166
BUT I DO WHAT I CAN FOR THE KIDS
HERE AT THE HOSPITAL.

29:30.250 --> 29:32.291
YOU MIGHT BE A GREAT NURSE,

29:32.375 --> 29:33.875
BUT YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT IT'S LIKE TO BE A MOTHER.

29:35.375 --> 29:37.208
I DON'T NEED
ANYBODY'S HELP.

29:40.792 --> 29:42.542
♪ TURN UP THE NIGHT ♪

29:42.625 --> 29:44.333
HI.

29:44.417 --> 29:45.667
WHERE YOU BEEN?

29:45.750 --> 29:46.917
OH, HI.
I JUST MET THESE GIRLS.

29:47.000 --> 29:48.250
THIS IS BROOKLYN,
AND THAT'S BECKY.

29:48.333 --> 29:49.250
HI.
HOW YOU DOING?

29:49.333 --> 29:51.000
HEY.

29:52.041 --> 29:53.709
YOU SMELL LIKE SMOKE.

29:53.792 --> 29:57.375
BROOKLYN SMOKES, AND I WENT
OUTSIDE WITH HER, SO...

29:58.875 --> 30:00.667
[ MICROPHONE FEEDBACK ]

30:00.750 --> 30:02.625
Man: WELCOME, STUDENTS,

30:02.709 --> 30:05.667
TO PARADISE COVE'S MOST
HEARTFELT CROWNING CEREMONY YET.

30:05.750 --> 30:07.291
I ASK YOU, WHAT MAKES A QUEEN?

30:07.375 --> 30:10.500
COURAGE, FEARLESSNESS,
KINDNESS,

30:10.583 --> 30:12.458
AND AN ACNE-FREE COMPLEXION.

30:12.542 --> 30:14.166
[ LIGHT LAUGHTER ]

30:14.250 --> 30:17.166
KARA SOUDERS
IS ALL OF THESE THINGS,

30:17.250 --> 30:19.959
BUT WHAT IS MOST SPECIAL
ABOUT KARA IS HER HEART,

30:20.041 --> 30:22.458
AND BEFORE WE CROWN HER
QUEEN OF OUR HEARTS,

30:22.542 --> 30:25.291
PARADISE COVE'S
SPIRITED CHEER SQUAD

30:25.375 --> 30:28.000
HAS PUT TOGETHER A TRIBUTE VIDEO
TO HONOR KARA.

30:28.083 --> 30:29.834
HEY!
HOLD ON, UH, ONE SEC.

30:29.917 --> 30:31.709
I GOT TO, UM --
I GOT TO SAY SOMETHING.

30:31.792 --> 30:33.166
I KNOW HOW YOU FEEL.

30:33.250 --> 30:35.417
ONCE YOU START THE LOVE,
IT'S HARD TO STOP.

30:35.500 --> 30:36.583
COME ON UP HERE, SON.

30:36.667 --> 30:39.291
[ STUDENTS MURMURING ]

30:41.375 --> 30:42.875
[ MICROPHONE FEEDBACK ]

30:42.959 --> 30:44.709
A FEW WORDS ON KARA SOUDERS.

30:44.792 --> 30:47.417
I'VE ONLY KNOWN HER
FOR FIVE DAYS,

30:47.500 --> 30:51.583
BUT WHAT I'VE LEARNED
IS THAT FIVE DAYS WITH KARA...

30:51.667 --> 30:54.125
IS FIVE DAYS TOO MANY...

30:54.208 --> 30:55.542
Young man: WHAT?!

30:55.625 --> 30:57.709
...BECAUSE KARA
IS THE BIGGEST BITCH

30:57.792 --> 30:59.500
I'VE EVER MET IN MY ENTIRE LIFE!

30:59.583 --> 31:00.959
ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.
LET'S GET THE SLIDE SHOW GOING.

31:01.041 --> 31:03.208
IT'S TRUE.
SHE'S -- SHE'S NOT A QUEEN.

31:03.291 --> 31:07.709
SHE'S A DICTATOR.
COLD, SELFISH, TYRANNICAL.

31:07.792 --> 31:10.125
SHE DOES NOT DESERVE
YOUR COMPASSION

31:10.208 --> 31:13.000
AND, MOST OF ALL,
DOES NOT DESERVE THIS CROWN.

31:13.083 --> 31:14.417
[ SCATTERED APPLAUSE ]

31:17.041 --> 31:18.542
<i>THE THING ABOUT BEING A HERO --</i>

31:18.625 --> 31:20.041
<i>YOU'RE NOT SUPPOSED TO RESCUE</i>

31:20.125 --> 31:21.667
<i>MORE THAN ONE DAMSEL</i>
<i>IN A NIGHT.</i>

31:25.166 --> 31:26.333
[ CHUCKLES ]

31:26.417 --> 31:27.917
OKAY.
OUT OF MY WAY.

31:28.000 --> 31:30.166
I'M A REGISTERED NURSE.

31:30.250 --> 31:33.875
THIS IS AN EMBARRASSMENT
OF RICHES, MAN.

31:33.959 --> 31:35.667
WAIT.

31:38.583 --> 31:40.917
YO, J-MAN. YOU OKAY?

31:41.000 --> 31:43.792
I DON'T KNOW, MAN.
I-I DON'T FEEL GOOD.

31:43.875 --> 31:46.166
JUST WAIT RIGHT HERE.
I'M GONNA GO GET YOU SOME WATER.

31:46.250 --> 31:48.500
NO, DON'T --

31:54.291 --> 31:56.208
[ TOILET FLUSHES ]
COME ON.

31:59.041 --> 32:01.000
OH, MY GOD.

32:01.083 --> 32:03.166
SOMETHING'S REALLY WRONG
WITH HIM. HE NEEDS A DOCTOR.

32:03.250 --> 32:04.500
IT'S THE CHEMO.

32:04.583 --> 32:06.959
THIS IS JUST
ONE OF THE SIDE EFFECTS.

32:12.125 --> 32:13.709
THOSE STUPID PAMPHLETS
YOU GAVE ME SAID

32:13.792 --> 32:15.458
HE WOULDN'T BE SICK
IN THE FIRST 24 HOURS.

32:15.542 --> 32:17.542
WELL, THAT IS OFTEN TRUE.

32:17.625 --> 32:19.917
NO TWO CASES
ARE THE SAME.

32:20.000 --> 32:22.542
WE CAN NEVER PREDICT HOW
SOMEONE'S BODY'S GOING TO REACT.

32:22.625 --> 32:23.917
HOW LONG WILL THIS LAST?

32:24.000 --> 32:25.417
COULD BE AS LONG
AS HIS CHEMO REGIMEN.

32:26.417 --> 32:27.709
[ SIGHS ] THANK YOU.

32:27.792 --> 32:30.125
I'LL GET YOU
SOME MORE TOWELS.

32:34.458 --> 32:37.458
[ SIGHS ]

32:39.750 --> 32:42.667
[ CELLPHONE CHIMING ]

32:42.750 --> 32:44.709
OH, MY GOD! ENOUGH!

32:44.792 --> 32:46.500
[ CELLPHONE SHATTERS ]

32:46.583 --> 32:48.583
[ SIGHS ]
THAT'S BETTER.

32:52.041 --> 32:54.083
SO, WHAT'D YOU THINK?

32:54.166 --> 32:56.959
IT'S EXACTLY HOW I IMAGINED
HOMECOMING WOULD BE.

32:57.041 --> 32:59.750
<i>EVEN IF YOU ARE JUST FRIENDS,</i>

32:59.834 --> 33:02.625
<i>THE RULE IS YOU DANCE</i>
<i>WITH THE GIRL YOU BROUGHT.</i>

33:15.792 --> 33:18.792
ARE YOU SURE
YOU DON'T WANT ANYTHING?

33:18.875 --> 33:21.417
ANOTHER BLANKET?
SOME SNACKS?

33:21.500 --> 33:23.125
NO, I'M -- I'M GOOD.

33:23.208 --> 33:24.709
JUST SIT WITH ME.

33:42.625 --> 33:43.875
YOU KNOW WHAT?

33:43.959 --> 33:45.750
I'M GONNA BRING YOU
A GINGER ALE.

33:45.834 --> 33:47.792
THE CARBONATION MIGHT BE GOOD
FOR YOUR STOMACH.

33:47.875 --> 33:50.208
MOM. I DON'T --
I DON'T WANT A GINGER ALE.

33:50.291 --> 33:53.166
MAYBE NOT NOW. FOR LATER.

33:53.250 --> 33:55.375
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK,
OKAY?

34:17.083 --> 34:18.750
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]

34:25.417 --> 34:26.834
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

34:26.917 --> 34:29.375
YOU OKAY?

34:29.458 --> 34:31.250
WHY WOULDN'T I BE?

34:31.333 --> 34:33.458
<i>TRANSLATION --</i>
<i>"I'M SUPER PISSED AT YOU."</i>

34:33.542 --> 34:36.208
WELL, YOU DIDN'T SAY MUCH
ON THE DRIVE BACK.

34:38.417 --> 34:40.583
WHY DID YOU GO UP THERE
AND DEFEND KARA?

34:40.667 --> 34:42.583
'CAUSE SHE WAS HAVING
A BAD NIGHT.

34:42.667 --> 34:45.375
SHE DESERVES A BAD NIGHT, LEO.
SHE'S A BAD PERSON.

34:45.458 --> 34:48.500
MAYBE, BUT NO ONE DESERVES
TO BE PITIED.

34:48.583 --> 34:51.041
YOU DON'T UNDERSTAND THAT
BECAUSE --

34:51.125 --> 34:53.250
WELL,
NO ONE PITIES YOU, EMMA.

34:53.333 --> 34:56.959
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE
IN THIS HOSPITAL.

34:58.917 --> 35:00.750
YOU DON'T HAVE TO BE HERE.

35:00.834 --> 35:02.959
[ LUKE SITAL-SINGH'S
"NOTHING STAYS THE SAME" PLAYS ]

35:07.291 --> 35:11.166
♪ I CAN TASTE IT IN MY MOUTH ♪

35:14.041 --> 35:18.500
♪ I AM HANGING UPSIDE DOWN ♪

35:20.583 --> 35:25.125
♪ ALL THE FACES
GATHERED 'ROUND ♪

35:26.250 --> 35:29.417
♪ TO WAIT AND SEE ♪

35:29.500 --> 35:32.166
♪ TO BREATHE RELIEF ♪

35:32.250 --> 35:35.542
♪ TO CALL MY NAME ♪

35:35.625 --> 35:39.917
♪ FOR THE FIRST TIME ♪

35:40.000 --> 35:43.417
